FBIS3-14479 "drnes060yy_94003" FBIS-NES-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Discussions Continue at G-15 Summit in New Delhi East Asia Growth Area Concept Discussed BK2903105594 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0731 GMT 29 Mar 94 BK2903105594 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] New Delhi, March 29 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- President Suharto of Indonesia supports the concept of the East Asia Growth Area (EAGA) encompassing Indonesia, the Philippines, Brunei and Malaysia Malaysian Prime Minister Dr. Mahathir Mohamed said Tuesday [29 March]. Mahathir said he explained the concept to Suharto during bilateral talks here Monday. Both are here to attend the three-day fourth summit of the Group of 15 developing countries which began Monday. Dr. Mahathir said he informed Suharto that Philippine President Fidel Ramos had also agreed to the concept, initiated by Malaysia for the mutual benefit of the countries involved. Dr. Mahathir and Suharto also discussed the need to reduce airport landing fees to promote cross border travel between the two countries. Also discussed was the question of greater air links among South countries to promote better contacts between their peoples.
